 And to do that, we'll use the extended Euclid algorithm.

30
00:01:26,460 --> 00:01:27,930
 In that case, often,

31
00:01:27,930 --> 00:01:30,930
 the algorithm will return the negative number and then

32
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:34,140
 we'll have to do a simple calculation in order to convert it to a number,

33
